'''Cao Xiwen''' (born 16 November 1983) is a [[Chinese people|Chinese]] actress.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.china.org.cn/culture/2009-07/06/content_18079434.htm |title=Actress Cao Xiwen |date= July 6, 2009|publisher= |work=China.org.cn }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://chinesemov.com/actors/Cao%20Xiwen.html |title=Cao Xiwen |accessdate= |publisher= |work= }}</ref> She is noted for her roles as [[Consort Xiao]] and [[List of Journey to the West characters|Gao Cuilan]] in the television series ''[[Beauty World (TV series)|Beauty World]]'' and ''[[Journey to the West (2010 TV series)|Journey to the West]]'' respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20071225/n254293189.shtml|script-title=zh:2007内地新人点将台 曹曦文在内敛中盛放|date=December 25, 2007|website=Sohu|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20070807/n251458246.shtml|script-title=zh:窈窕淑女“君”子好求 曹曦文青睐别克君越(图)|date=August 7, 2007|website=Sohu|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://yule.sohu.com/20080627/n257789166.shtml|script-title=zh:曹曦文闪耀荧屏戏路百变 女主角飙升收视率|date=June 27, 2008|website=Sohu|language=zh}}</ref>

==Early life==
Cao was born and raised in [[Jinhua]], [[Zhejiang]], where she attended the Zhejiang Arts School, majoring in music and dance.<ref name="cat" >{{cite web |url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/s/m/2008-08-01/13352124135.shtml |script-title=zh:岩女郎曹曦文忆家乡 遥想江南美丽风光(图) |date=2008 |publisher=Sina |work= |language=zh }}</ref> Cao entered [[Central Academy of Drama]] in 2004, majoring in acting, where she graduated in 2008.<ref name="cat" />

==Acting career==
Cao made her acting debut in ''My World is Beautiful, Because of You'' (2000), playing a secretary. Cao's first film role was uncredited appearance in the film ''Pearl Gown'' (2002).

In 2001, Cao had a minor role as Ding Xiang in the [[wuxia]] television series ''Treasure Raiders'', which starred [[Nicky Wu]] and [[Athena Chu]].

In 2007, Cao starred in the fantasy television series ''[[The Fairies of Liaozhai]]'', based on the novel ''[[Strange Stories from a Chinese Studio]]'' by [[Pu Songling]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/p/2007-08-14/14021675955.shtml|script-title=zh:《聊斋奇女子》让曹曦文从清纯到妩媚(组图)|date=April 14, 2007|website=Sina|language=zh}}</ref>

In 2008, Cao participated in ''[[Three Kingdoms (TV series)|Three Kingdoms]]'', a historical television series adapted from [[Luo Guanzhong]]'s classical novel ''[[Romance of the Three Kingdoms]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2010-05-26/21112970271.shtml |script-title=zh:新《三国》忙吹枕头风 曹曦文初扮歹毒女(图) |date=May 26, 2010 |publisher=Sina |work= |language=zh }}</ref> The series reached number one in the ratings when it aired in China. That same year, she received [[Huading Awards|Huading Award]] nomination for Best New Actress.

In 2009, Cao played the character [[List of Journey to the West characters|Gao Cuilan]] in ''[[Journey to the West (2010 TV series)|Journey to the West]]'', a [[shenmo]] television series adaptation based on the novel of [[Journey to the West|the same name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.163.com/10/0226/15/60F5P7LU00031GVS.html |script-title=zh:《西游记》剧照曝光 曹曦文倾情演绎"人猪情"|date= February 26, 2010|publisher=Netease |work= |language=zh }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2010-02-24/11242880915.shtml |script-title=zh:曹曦文《西游记》情定八戒 "人猪之恋"成话题|date=February 24, 2010 |publisher=Sina |work= |language=zh }}</ref> 

In 2010, Cao starred  in the [[Tang Dynasty|historical]] romance television series ''[[Beauty World (TV series)|Beauty World]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20110107/000394.htm |script-title=zh:曹曦文《美人天下》耍狠 诠释心计女很过瘾 |date=January 7, 2011 |publisher=Tencent |work= |language=zh }}</ref>

In 2011, Cao headlined the hit drama ''Wild Duck''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.qq.com/a/20110414/000351.htm|script-title=zh:《野鸭子》破浙江收视 曹曦文四戏连播好戏不断|date=April 14, 2011|website=Tencent|language=zh}}</ref> Cao was nominated for the [[Flying Apsaras Award]] for Best Actress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jhnews.com.cn/zzxb/2011-08/19/content_1808693.htm|script-title=zh:准影后曹曦文：最骄傲，我是金华人|date=August 19, 2011|website=JHnews|language=zh}}</ref>

In 2012, Cao reprised her role as in the ''Wild Duck'' sequel, ''Wild Duck 2'', the series was one of the most watched ones in mainland China in that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/s/m/2011-05-27/15033319776.shtml |script-title=zh:曹曦文：因放得开而纯情 野不是本色但从不装|quote =作为2011年央视八套开年大戏，《野鸭子》缔造了央视收视史上的一个奇迹：首播即以平均收视率3.2创下了央视八套近年来最高收视率的纪录，央八在一个月内循环播出三遍，而央一又紧接着在重播第四遍，如此滚动播放的频率在央视堪称“前无古人”。|date=May 27, 2011 |publisher=Sina |work= |language=zh }}</ref>

==Personal life==
Cao dated [[Chen Sicheng]] in September 2008, they split in March 2011.<ref name="duck">{{cite web|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/yzyd/ent/20140410/c_1110190137.htm |script-title=zh:31岁曹曦文低调产子 与陈思诚分手后嫁给富商 |date=April 10, 2014 |publisher=Xinhuanet |work= |language=zh }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

In 2012, Cao was married to a Taiwanese businessman and had a daughter. They had divorced in 2014.<ref name="duck" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ent.163.com/14/0708/13/A0KRQPRB000333J5.html|script-title=zh:曹曦文情史坎坷 曾嫁黑社会富商|date=July 28, 2014|website=Netease|language=zh}}</ref>

